Config/benchmark/override-cores-command:
    cd /Users/4482173/Documents/GitHub/alfakR
    Rscript -e 'pkgload::load_all(".", quiet = TRUE); rmarkdown::render("benchmark/scr/run_benchmark_alfak.Rmd", params = list(n_cores = 12))'
Config/benchmark/defaults:
    The benchmark Rmd defaults to run_benchmark = TRUE, force_refit = FALSE,
    n_cores = 9, and cohort_transition_version = "contextual".
Config/benchmark/behavior:
    The command loads the current checkout with pkgload::load_all(), so it uses
    this repository's source code rather than an already installed alfakR
    package. Existing complete and version-compatible fit outputs are reused;
    missing or incompatible outputs are run. Regular nn_prior tasks are
    parallelized with n_cores. cohort_transition/contextual first learns one
    cohort prior per pm x minobs group, then parallelizes per-patient contextual
    refits with the same n_cores value on Unix platforms.
Config/benchmark/output:
    The default HTML report is written next to
    benchmark/scr/run_benchmark_alfak.Rmd. Fit outputs are written under
    benchmark/results/fits.
